  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Virtual Cash Terminals (VCTs) track cash flow and card payments on tickets, helping ensure accurate register balancing at the end of the day. Our optional integrated Payment systems give users a secure solution for accepting payments on a payment terminal and seamlessly posting those transactions to a RepairQ ticket. This streamlines the checkout process and reduces accounting errors compared to manually recording payments.</p><p>VCTs are now optional to accommodate varied business needs, allowing transactions to be recorded outside our software. Two new settings enable users to customize the ticket closure process without requiring a VCT or payment, ensuring that inventory is still managed effectively within RepairQ.</p><p>If you open a VCT, it must be closed daily for cash reconciliation. This process, handled by Shift Leads or Managers, should be performed on each computer or device paired to a VCT. Closing your VCT daily helps reconcile cash counts and audit for payment discrepancies. </p><p><strong>Note</strong>: VCTs and cash reconciliation do not contribute to sales or COGS reporting, as this information is pulled directly from ticket data. They should not be used to calculate sales projections.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Control - f79824.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2717089793/Control%20-%20f79824.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"VirtualCashTerminal(VCT)Resources-VCTManagementSettings\">VCT Management Settings</h2><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/2348187679\" rel=\"nofollow\">Virtual Cash Terminal: Ticket Payment Settings</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933901843\" rel=\"nofollow\">Setting up a Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT)</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/2717712385\" rel=\"nofollow\">Currency Options for Cash Transactions</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/2713124902\" rel=\"nofollow\">Cash Rounding for Transactions</a></p></li></ul><h2 id=\"VirtualCashTerminal(VCT)Resources-VCTOperationsandReporting\">VCT Operations and Reporting</h2><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933639827\" rel=\"nofollow\">Assign a Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT) to Accept Payments</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933803641\" rel=\"nofollow\">Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT) Cash Transfers</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933541639\" rel=\"nofollow\">Closing a Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT)</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1934229524\" rel=\"nofollow\">Reports: Cash Reconciliation</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1934295071\" rel=\"nofollow\">Reports: Cash Flow</a></p></li></ul><h2 id=\"VirtualCashTerminal(VCT)Resources-ReceiptandInvoicePrinting\">Receipt and Invoice Printing</h2><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1932361958\" rel=\"nofollow\">Print Settings - Receipt Template</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933377656\" rel=\"nofollow\">Print Settings - Invoices</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933869057\" rel=\"nofollow\">Recommended Hardware Troubleshooting Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933541484\" rel=\"nofollow\">Configuring a Cash Drawer to Open Automatically When a Receipt is Printed</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1936588827\" rel=\"nofollow\">QZ Printing System Requirements and Printer Settings</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1934229707\" rel=\"nofollow\">QZ Integrated Printing - Start Here!</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1936949301\" rel=\"nofollow\">Integrated Printing Troubleshooting</a></p></li></ul><h2 id=\"VirtualCashTerminal(VCT)Resources-IntegratedPayments\">Integrated Payments</h2><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1934295157\" rel=\"nofollow\">Integrated Payment Processing - Start Here!</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1934229721\" rel=\"nofollow\">Integrated Payments: Troubleshooting Resources</a></p></li></ul><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
